cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses an algorithmic framework for estimating the operational topology and statistics of injections in radial distribution grids under limited availability of nodal voltage measurements. This involves the use of novel ordered trends in voltage magnitude fluctuations at node groups, which suggests a focus on system identification and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the computational complexity of the designed algorithms, which suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper validates the performance of the algorithms using both linearized and non-linear ac power flow samples in test distribution grids, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
